observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to the following:
Mobilize additional competent personnel from other departments as members and completely conduct physical count of Inventory of the Municipality’s PPE annually and submit to the Office of the Auditor the duly accomplished RPCPPE of all PPE accounts;
To direct the Municipal Accountant and designated General Services Officer reconcile and analyze the difference between ledger and RPCPPE report and effect necessary adjustments;
Instruct the General Services Office to transfer all identified unserviceable properties in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property Form as prescribed in Annex 51, Volume 2 of the Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, for proper disposal and basis to derecognize from the book of accounts, then undertake necessary actions for disposal in accordance with Section 79 of PD 1445;
To require the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal GSO maintain Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC) and Property Cards for each group of PPEs, respectively and reconciliation between these two records shall be undertaken regularly; and
In response to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 and EO No. 2023-32, conduct one-time cleansing of the Municipality’s PPE to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability.

Require the BAC to undergo procurement process in hiring consultants;

Submit reports on the LGU’s situation during the time of hiring the consultants with specific details which gives rise to the necessity of hiring the consultants;

Submit specific and justifiable Consultancy Progress Reports or any form of accomplishment report for each month of CY 2022 to check whether the purpose for hiring consultants were actually achieved for further verification;

Submit copies of Professional License or Curriculum Vitae or any proof that BAC had evaluate the qualifications and expertise of the hired consultants;

All contracts and each of all documents forming part thereof should be submitted to the Office of the Auditor within five calendar days from the date of execution.

Management appropriate fund for the titling of all land;

The LCE direct the Municipal Assessor̕ s Office to exert effort in titling the land owned by the Municipality;

The LCE require the Accounting Office to set up and maintain complete accounting records; 

The LCE require the Treasurer̕ s Office/GSO to keep on file complete records of real properties; and,

The LCE direct the Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of all the parcels of land owned by the Municipality and reconcile with the books for proper presentation in the FS.

